The paper focuses on vehicle tracking using multimodal data fusion, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques for vehicle detection and tracking, robotics (RO) for surveillance cameras, machine learning (LG) for the Kalman filter and data fusion, multimedia (MM) for image processing, and artificial intelligence (AI) for the overall framework design. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV, followed by cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.MM, and cs.AI.
